news.title: Goa: Sao Jose de Areal locals oppose land use change
news.para: “No land use change shall be allowed except for individual houses for local residents and indigent citizens and schools, hospitals, markets, jogging parks, playgrounds for locals,” the resolution read.

news.title: Punjab CM launches scheme to give property rights to people living within 'lal lakir'
news.para: Punjab chief minister Charanjit Singh Channi said that earlier this scheme was launched only for the residents of villages but now it is being extended to the eligible residents of the cities within the 'lal lakir'.

news.title: Minister tells officials to note demands for rehabilitation of Chikhali, Ambewadi residents
news.para: Satej Patil, the district guardian minister, has instructed the authorities to take note of the villagers’ demands, especially related to the plot requirement for permanent settlement.

news.title: BEE to adopt Indo-Swiss technology to construct 28 lakh houses in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: The BEEP project is aimed at adopting ‘Indo-Swiss energy efficient building technology’ to promote energy-efficient building design in the construction of the proposed 28 lakh houses in Andhra Pradesh.

news.title: Haryana CM directs HSVP to repair flats in Gurugram's Sector 47
news.para: He also asked the officials to prepare a list of beneficiaries and allot these flats to them within the stipulated time. To rehabilitate slum dwellers, HSVP had constructed a total of 1,088 cheap flats in 2011 and 2015.

news.title: Mhada gives affordable housing, entitled to tax relief: ITAT
news.para: Mhada, a statutory housi-ng authority engaged in providing affordable housing, had appealed to the ITAT as it was denied tax exemption for 2014-15.

news.title: Why some buildings risk collapse in Bengaluru
news.para: “Most buildings in Bengaluru are not built professionally. Many builders do not consult structural engineers and other experts,” said Manjunath VK, professor at Ramaiah Institute of Technology.​

news.title: RERA directs Chhattisgarh housing board to develop amenities at its project
news.para: Besides, the board has been directed to firefighting systems at Pine and Camelia category buildings and to repair the damaged roads and boundary walls within two months.

news.title: Bank of India cuts home loan rates to 6.50%
news.para: ​​With this cut, the interest rate on home loans starts at 6.50 per cent against earlier 6.85 per cent, and at 6.85 per cent against 7.35 per cent prior on vehicle loans, the bank said in a release.

news.title: Salman Khan pays Rs 8.25 lakh monthly rent for a duplex in Bandra
news.para: ​According to a real estate portal, Salman Khan Ventures Private Limited has renewed a rent agreement for a duplex on the 17th and 18th floor of Bandra's Maqba Heights, which is owned by Baba Siddique and Zeeshan Siddique.

news.title: Greater Noida development body launches plot scheme for EWS
news.para: he scheme includes a plot of 23,500 sqm in Sector Zeta 1, a plot of 28,265 sqm in Sector Eta 2 and two plots of 39,321 sqm and 30,000 sqm in Sector Sigma 3.

news.title: Trimble leases three lakh sq ft office space in Chennai
news.para: "The office move is part of a longer term strategic commitment to India by Trimble management for growth in captive R&D services as well as customer base," said Rajan Aiyer, managing director, Trimble, South Asia Region.

news.title: Cisco renews lease pact for over 2.7-million-sq-ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: San Jose-headquartered company has entered into an agreement with the Blackstone Group-entity Nucleus Office Parks to renew the lease at its Cessna Business Parks at Outer Ring Road in Bangalore.

news.title: Nagpur civic body collects Rs 97.42 crore property tax during Apr-Sept 2021
news.para: Property tax department’s poor performance continued. To stay abreast with the target of Rs289.43 crore, NMC should have generated Rs144.71 crore, but created only Rs97.42 crore.

news.title: Goa: Sand mining in Chapora river can resume in four zones
news.para: SEIAA has asked for further scientific studies to be carried out in the case of two other zones in the Chapora. Applications were received from the North Goa collector for six zones in the river for sand mining.
